Authentication Flow: 1. Client sends JWT in Authorization header 2.

4
00:00:18,276 --> 00:00:25,460
Gateway validates JWT signature (using public key, no DB call) 3.

5
00:00:25,460 --> 00:00:30,210
Gateway extracts userId, role from token 4.

6
00:00:30,210 --> 00:00:35,328
Gateway adds X-User-Id and X-User-Role headers 5.

7
00:00:35,328 --> 00:00:47,657
Services read these headers (trust gateway) Plot twist: ChatGPT uses the exact same concepts we're learning here to handle millions of concurrent users.

